<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Supplication said Upon Completing the Recitation of the Quraan During Taraawih Has No Basis Whatsoever]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1260&amp;p=1332#p1332"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">The Supplication said Upon Completing the Recitation of the Quraan During Taraawih Has No Basis Whatsoever - Shaykh Al-Albaani [1420H]</span></strong><br /><br />Questioner: The supplication said upon completing the recitation of the Quraan, especially during taraawih, does it have any basis?<br /><br />Al-Albaani: No, it has no basis.<br /><br />Questioner: The supplication said when one finishes reciting the Quraan?<br /><br />Al-Albaani: Upon completing the recitation of the Quraan … when a Muslim finishes [reciting all of it], it is a Sunnah for him to, or it is mustahab for him to supplicate and gather his family to do so.<br /><br />As for when the Quraan is completed like this in the prayer, in the night prayer, then this long, extensive du’aa has no basis whatsoever.<br /><br />Rihlatun-Noor, 19.<br /><br />Also see Shaikh Uthaimeen’s answer on the same topic here.<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://shaikhalbaani.wordpress.com/2015/07/08/the-supplication-said-upon-completing-the-recitation-of-the-quraan-during-taraawih-has-no-basis-whatsoever/">https://shaikhalbaani.wordpress.com/201 ... hatsoever/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Thu Mar 09, 2017 12:14 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
